						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Broken slab built into the window of the raṅgamaṇḍapa in the Śaṁbhuliṅga temple.</hi></p>						

						<p>Sōvidēva—(Date lost).</p>						

						<p>The record is damaged and worn out and the date is only partially preserved, <hi rend="italic">i.e.</hi> <hi rend="bold">Friday, lunar eclipse.</hi></p>						

						<p>The inscription seems to state that the king made a gift of land for the worship of god Svayaṁbhū and for the feeding of the ascetics, at the request of Mahāpradhāna <hi rend="bold">Lakshmidhara-daṇḍanāyaka</hi> and others.</p>						

						</summary>
